0.name: Image

teams.name: Rocket Head and the Invisible Jackets

0.deck: Image Comics was founded in 1992 by a group of high-profile comic book writers and artists, as a way to publish stories owned by creators rather than the company itself. They are now one of the largest comic book publishers in the United States.

1.name: Boom! Studios

teams.name: Doctor Teeth and the Electric Mayhem

1.deck: BOOM! Studios is a large independent comic book company founded in 2005 and based in Los Angeles, California, USA.

2.name: Valiant
2.deck: Valiant Comics began as an imprint of Voyager Communications, established in 1989 in part by former Marvel editor-in-chief Jim Shooter. It was discontinued in 1994 after being bought out by Acclaim Entertainment. After Acclaim closed its doors in 2004, the publisher was revived as Valiant Entertainment and has been publishing new material since May 2012.

4.name: Dark Horse Comics

teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

4.deck: Dark Horse Comics is one of the largest independent comic book publishers, best known for Hellboy and various Star Wars titles.

5.name: Dell
5.deck: Also Known as Dell Comics Group and Dell Super Comics Group was an American publisher of books and comic books, founded in 1921. They would partner with Western Publishing from 1938 to 1962. Dell was bought by Random House and is now part of the "Bantam Dell Publishing Group".

6.name: Fiction House

teams.name: White Hunters of the African Safari

6.deck: A pulp magazine and comic book publisher in the Golden Age of Comics.

7.name: Top Cow

teams.name: The Real Super Hero Team of America

7.deck: Top Cow Productions (a comic book publisher partnered with Image Comics) is best known for titles such as Cyberforce, The Darkness, and Witchblade.

8.name: IDW Publishing

teams.name: Wolfram and Hart, Attorneys at Law
The Beauty and the Beast Unit

8.deck: IDW Publishing (Idea   Design Works, LLC) is a comic book publisher known for Steve Niles’ horror title 30 Days of Night. It has grown to include both original series as well as licensed property.

9.name: Vertigo

teams.name: The Vassals of the Morning Star

9.deck: Vertigo is an imprint of  DC Comics suggested for mature readers and is a continuity separate from the DC Universe that has included Sandman, Swamp Thing, John Constantine (Hellblazer) and many others. However, nowadays the imprint is mostly focused upon creator-owned material.
